incidents.name: Increased Reports of HTTP/2 and HTTP/3 Errors

incident_updates.body: This incident is now resolved.
A fix for this issue has been implemented and we are currently monitoring the results.
We have identified the issue causing sporadic HTTP connection errors into Cloudflare, and we are rolling back the affected web serving systems to the last good state.

We have seen cases of connection failures affecting requests coming from both HTTP/2 and HTTP/3 clients for affected customers. We are continuing to investigate the root cause, and will have more information soon on specific services or regions that may be affected.
We have an increased number of reports of QUIC protocol errors when calling Cloudflare services. We will provide more information soon on services or regions that may be affected.

incidents.name: Gateway File Sandboxing Issue

incident_updates.body: This issue is now resolved.

Cloudflare has identified and applied a fix for an issue where Gateway File Sandboxing was not being applied as expected.  We are currently monitoring the results.

The observed impact of this issue is that Sandboxing account setting are applied, if your account is set to fail open users will be able to download a file without Sandboxing applied. If set to fail closed, users will not be able to download the file.
